1
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:38,200
<i> Thank you, Love.</i>

2
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:40,233
<i>If it weren't
for your hard work,</i>

3
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:42,033
<i>our child wouldn't have
received an operation.</i>

4
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,633
<i>- Manuel?
- Who's that?</i>

5
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:45,433
<i> She's my coworker's cousin.</i>

6
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:47,133
<i>And that's the party
they attended.</i>

7
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,633
<i> Who's this?</i>

8
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,433
<i> The woman is clinging to you.</i>

9
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:51,467
<i> Is that Hazel?</i>

10
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:52,600
<i> Hello, Love?</i>

11
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:55,067
<i> Stop calling my husband love.</i>

12
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,267
<i> Did you call Felma?</i>

13
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:58,767
<i>Manuel, is that woman
telling the truth?</i>

14
00:00:58,900 --> 00:01:00,633
<i>Felma, wait.
Let me explain.</i>

15
00:01:00,767 --> 00:01:02,233
<i> Answer my question!</i>

16
00:01:02,367 --> 00:01:03,533
<i> He wanted to marry me!</i>

17
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:04,600
<i>- Hazel!
- Did you hear that?</i>

18
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:05,800
<i> Because I'm pregnant!</i>

19
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,333
<i> Listen, I'll do something.</i>

20
00:01:08,467 --> 00:01:09,400
<i> I'll fix this.</i>

21
00:01:09,533 --> 00:01:10,800
<i> That's enough, Manuel.</i>

22
00:01:10,933 --> 00:01:12,267
<i> Let's put an end to this.</i>

23
00:01:14,567 --> 00:01:17,300
<i>So that's the reason he doesn't
call me often anymore.</i>

24
00:01:17,433 --> 00:01:20,000
<i>Because he's busy
with his new family.</i>

25
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:22,400
<i>How will you tell the kids
about it?</i>

26
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:24,300
<i> The kids shouldn't know.</i>

27
00:01:29,767 --> 00:01:31,533
You've got nice shoes!

28
00:01:31,667 --> 00:01:33,767
- There!
- Hey!

29
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,033
Oh my!

30
00:01:35,167 --> 00:01:36,133
It didn't hit your shoes!

31
00:01:36,267 --> 00:01:38,333
- Look.
- Look, it's close.

32
00:01:38,467 --> 00:01:40,300
Jopet has new shoes.

33
00:01:40,467 --> 00:01:41,500
He's bragging about it.

34
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:43,800
Isn't it cool?

35
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,067
My dad gave it to me.

36
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:48,967
He said he'd give me more when
he comes home for Christmas.

37
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:50,900
I'll ask my dad to buy me
the same shoes.

38
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:52,433
A gift when he comes home.

39
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:57,467
How will he come home?

40
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:59,000
You no longer have a dad.

41
00:02:00,133 --> 00:02:00,867
What do you mean?

42
00:02:01,467 --> 00:02:03,467
He had another child
in Saudi Arabia.

43
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:04,633
That's the reason.

44
00:02:06,367 --> 00:02:08,200
What child are you
talking about, Jopet?

45
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:12,467
He got another woman pregnant.

46
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:13,733
Cool, isn't it?

47
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,400
That's not true.

48
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:17,767
Take it back!
Take it back!

49
00:02:18,233 --> 00:02:19,667
Mayette told me about it.

50
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:21,900
She said your dad would
never come home.

51
00:02:22,033 --> 00:02:23,067
Is that so?

52
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,633
Go ahead, fight him! Hit him!

53
00:02:25,767 --> 00:02:27,800
Give him more! Go on!

54
00:02:27,933 --> 00:02:29,300
You can do it!

55
00:02:29,433 --> 00:02:31,833
- You can do it!
- That's enough!

56
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:34,067
What? Huh?

57
00:02:34,467 --> 00:02:36,167
- Stop!
- What?

58
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:37,800
You behave like that
because you don't have a father!

59
00:02:39,867 --> 00:02:42,367
- You're fatherless!
- What do you mean?

60
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,233
What do you mean? Huh?

61
00:02:44,367 --> 00:02:45,533
That's enough!

62
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:48,200
That's enough!

63
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:58,500
Felma, I cooked dinner
for you and the kids.

64
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:14,300
- Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

65
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:16,767
Okay, I'll cook dinner
for us first.

66
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:18,733
Then I'll come back here, okay?

67
00:03:21,767 --> 00:03:23,733
I'll be quick.

68
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,933
Text me if you need anything.

69
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:27,833
What's going on?

70
00:03:27,967 --> 00:03:28,933
Jeff!

71
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,233
Son! Son, come here.

72
00:03:31,467 --> 00:03:32,733
What happened? Wait!

73
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:35,000
Did you get into a fight?

74
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,933
Andeng, what happened?

75
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:38,733
Why did your brother
look like that?

76
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:43,067
Mom, is it true?

77
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:44,833
What is?

78
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:47,533
Did dad have another child?

79
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:52,400
Does he have a new family now?

80
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,367
<i>- Hazel!
- Wait a second.</i>

81
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:11,633
Who is it?

82
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:13,067
<i> Hazel!</i>

83
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:15,133
Abel? Is that you?

84
00:04:15,267 --> 00:04:17,167
- Wait.
- Hazel!

85
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:20,033
Oh! What happened?

86
00:04:20,167 --> 00:04:21,367
Hold on, wait.

87
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:22,667
Come in, come in.

88
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:24,133
What's wrong with him?

89
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,567
He was drunk. What else?

90
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:27,867
- Oh.
- What?

91
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,833
Lay him down on the sofa.

92
00:04:31,433 --> 00:04:32,500
Be careful.
Lay him down on the sofa.

93
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:36,333
What happened?

94
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:39,067
I was about to leave.

95
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:41,767
I was planning to find a way to
pick him up from your apartment.

96
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:43,367
I'm glad you were able
to bring him back here.

97
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:49,433
What happened?

98
00:04:51,867 --> 00:04:53,300
<i> Mom, answer me.</i>

99
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:57,067
Does dad already have
a new family?

100
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,700
What's wrong with you, kids?

101
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:01,867
Why do you listen to gossip?

102
00:05:02,033 --> 00:05:04,833
Whose loose tongue
did you hear that from?

103
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:09,133
We heard it from Jopet.

104
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,400
He said he got the news
from Mayette.

105
00:05:12,967 --> 00:05:15,800
She heard you and Uncle Abel
talking.

106
00:05:16,633 --> 00:05:18,633
That's why Jeff and I
got into a fight!

107
00:05:18,767 --> 00:05:20,200
Oh, my God.

108
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:22,033
My God. My God, Felma.

109
00:05:22,167 --> 00:05:25,367
Your goddaughter
is such a tattletale.

110
00:05:26,433 --> 00:05:29,733
Mom, tell us the truth.

111
00:05:30,933 --> 00:05:33,167
Does dad have a new family?

112
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,300
It's true, my children.

113
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:56,000
Your dad already
has a new family.

114
00:06:09,967 --> 00:06:11,333
<i> What happened?</i>

115
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:15,233
He took his anger out
on the walls of my apartment.

116
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:18,300
Why didn't you stop him?

117
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:22,700
- I don't want to get hit...
- And you even drank.

118
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:24,633
You should've told him
to go home instead.

119
00:06:24,767 --> 00:06:26,967
He wanted to get wasted.
What else can I do?

120
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:28,667
And you let him!

121
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,667
Just admit that you wanted
to drink, too.

122
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,833
You're an enabler.

123
00:06:34,133 --> 00:06:35,700
Why are you getting mad at me?

124
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:37,367
Why are you all so furious
at me?

125
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,033
I have nothing to do with that!

126
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:40,600
You and your husband
should talk!

127
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:42,067
Talk things out!

128
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,533
Why are you getting me involved?
It's unbelievable!

129
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:45,733
- I'm leaving!
- Are you blaming me?

130
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:00,400
Dad has another woman.

131
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:03,900
And he's even having a baby.

132
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:07,900
Can dad really do that, Mom?

133
00:07:08,567 --> 00:07:10,200
Is that why you had a fight?

134
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:12,533
Is that why he is no longer
calling us?

135
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:18,167
He's already busy
with that woman named Hazel.

136
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:24,633
They're having a baby.

137
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:32,067
Hazel?

138
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:33,900
<i> The nurse?</i>

139
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:37,033
I thought
she was only dad's friend?

140
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:40,533
He's fooling us!

141
00:07:42,667 --> 00:07:44,733
Doesn't dad love you anymore?

142
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,067
I don't know.

143
00:07:50,867 --> 00:07:51,800
What about us?

144
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:54,433
Does he not love us anymore?

145
00:07:54,567 --> 00:07:55,233
Dear.

146
00:07:56,233 --> 00:07:56,967
Dear...

147
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:58,433
come here.

148
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:00,467
Your dad loves you both.

149
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,400
Mom...

150
00:08:02,767 --> 00:08:05,067
dad promised he would come home.

151
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,467
He'll fulfill it.

152
00:08:07,967 --> 00:08:10,133
You shouldn't have fought
with him!

153
00:08:10,633 --> 00:08:12,733
Stop blaming mom!

154
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:14,367
It's dad's fault!

155
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:16,367
Why?

156
00:08:19,233 --> 00:08:20,000
Mom.

157
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,200
Why did you allow it to happen?

158
00:08:23,433 --> 00:08:26,967
You are his wife.
Take him back from that Hazel.

159
00:08:29,033 --> 00:08:30,200
He's right, Mom.

160
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:33,067
Take dad back.

161
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:39,533
My dear children,

162
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,600
I can't do that.

163
00:08:43,467 --> 00:08:45,400
That's not possible, dear.

164
00:08:45,533 --> 00:08:47,733
He's married to that woman.

165
00:08:51,533 --> 00:08:52,867
He got married?

166
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,167
But you two are married.

167
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:57,600
Is that possible?

168
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:08,233
Your dad and I are not married.

169
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:25,833
So...

170
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:28,033
who's tending to your wound now?

171
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,767
Is it your ex?

172
00:09:30,967 --> 00:09:31,800
No, right?

173
00:09:33,367 --> 00:09:34,100
It's me!

174
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:35,567
Your wife!

175
00:09:36,133 --> 00:09:38,433
You gave me hell
over that woman.

176
00:09:39,133 --> 00:09:40,633
Now look, where is she?

177
00:09:40,767 --> 00:09:42,500
Where's that Felma? Nowhere!

178
00:09:43,633 --> 00:09:44,633
I really hope you're seeing

179
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:47,333
all the effort I'm putting in
right now.

180
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,700
So, are you going to do
it again?

181
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:55,667
Will you talk to Felma again?

182
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:57,700
Don't get yourself caught.

183
00:09:57,833 --> 00:09:59,300
I'll make sure

184
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,467
that that wound won't be
the only thing you'll get.

185
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,700
<i> You're not married to dad?</i>

186
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:14,500
Why?

187
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:22,700
Because we prioritized
the more important things.

188
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:24,600
Your schooling,

189
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:27,800
our daily expenses,

190
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:30,600
and your medicines, dear.

191
00:10:30,733 --> 00:10:32,467
All your necessities.

192
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,500
But, Mom...

193
00:10:35,133 --> 00:10:37,033
will getting married
cost you a lot?

194
00:10:37,167 --> 00:10:40,367
Because if not, you and dad
should've gotten married!

195
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,333
Hey, Andrea!

196
00:10:41,467 --> 00:10:43,067
Stop blaming mom!

197
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:43,933
Why?

198
00:10:44,433 --> 00:10:46,367
It's her fault!

199
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:50,533
She was acting like dad's wife,
but she was just pretending!

200
00:10:50,667 --> 00:10:53,067
- Andeng, that's enough!
- Dad is a liar!

201
00:10:53,567 --> 00:10:54,600
We all thought he was working.

202
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:56,000
It turns out
he was already womanizing!

203
00:10:56,133 --> 00:10:57,700
Dad isn't a womanizer!

204
00:10:57,833 --> 00:11:00,667
I don't believe in marriage.

205
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,833
You know what happened
to my parents, right?

206
00:11:03,967 --> 00:11:06,933
Your grandparents.

207
00:11:07,067 --> 00:11:11,500
They got married,
but broke up in the end.

208
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:13,733
There you go.

209
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,100
You don't want to get married.

210
00:11:15,233 --> 00:11:17,767
That's why dad married
another woman!

211
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:19,833
I'll call Dad.

212
00:11:19,967 --> 00:11:21,300
- I'll talk to him.
- Andeng, don't.

213
00:11:21,433 --> 00:11:22,333
Dear, no.

214
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:23,367
Andrea!

215
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:25,467
Dear, don't do that.
You'll only get hurt.

216
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,700
Andrea, listen to mom!

217
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,067
Andrea!

218
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,033
Andrea!

219
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:33,433
Why...

220
00:11:33,767 --> 00:11:34,867
why is it like this?

221
00:11:35,867 --> 00:11:37,633
Why can't I contact him?

222
00:11:37,767 --> 00:11:39,600
If he no longer wants
to talk to us,

223
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:41,267
then don't!

224
00:11:58,267 --> 00:11:59,233
Mom.

225
00:12:00,733 --> 00:12:02,000
Please stop crying.

226
00:12:03,533 --> 00:12:04,533
Please stop crying.

227
00:12:39,267 --> 00:12:41,100
What are you doing here again?

228
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,533
<i>Your wife will probably come
at me again</i>

229
00:12:43,667 --> 00:12:44,967
<i> if she finds out about this.</i>

230
00:12:45,267 --> 00:12:47,367
<i>She acts like some boss
in the way she talks.</i>

231
00:12:51,467 --> 00:12:53,233
Bro, I need to talk to Felma.

232
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:54,800
Bro...

233
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,733
she might not take your call.

234
00:12:57,867 --> 00:12:59,200
Cool things off for now.

235
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:01,300
I hurt her, Bro.

236
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,700
I only want to make sure
she's okay.

237
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:05,767
This is the first time
we've fought like this.

238
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:07,000
Whenever we fought before,

239
00:13:07,133 --> 00:13:08,933
we would fix things right away
for the sake of the kids.

240
00:13:11,067 --> 00:13:12,033
<i> And that's another thing.</i>

241
00:13:13,467 --> 00:13:15,700
How will I explain it
to the kids?

242
00:13:16,133 --> 00:13:16,833
Bro...

243
00:13:17,633 --> 00:13:18,700
they already know.

244
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:21,067
How?

245
00:13:23,233 --> 00:13:25,500
That's what only Paz told me.

246
00:13:26,633 --> 00:13:28,367
She said your family's
in some kind of a mess.

247
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:34,533
The more reason
I should talk to them, Bro.

248
00:13:44,467 --> 00:13:46,200
Felma. Felma!

249
00:13:46,333 --> 00:13:48,367
Manuel wants to talk to you.

250
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:49,833
Here.

251
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:52,500
We have nothing left
to talk about.

252
00:13:53,533 --> 00:13:56,033
Felma, you two should talk.

253
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,633
I'll talk to dad.

254
00:13:57,767 --> 00:13:59,233
- Hey!
- Andrea, wait.

255
00:13:59,367 --> 00:14:00,333
- Hello, Dad.
- Andrea!

256
00:14:00,467 --> 00:14:01,933
- Andrea, don't.
- Dad.

257
00:14:02,067 --> 00:14:03,233
Dear, don't. Don't do that.

258
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:04,600
Andeng, my dear?

259
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,967
- Don't talk to your dad.
- Dad, is it true?

260
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:08,100
Andrea.

261
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,700
- Give me that.
- Did you really marry

262
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:10,833
that Hazel?

263
00:14:11,867 --> 00:14:12,833
<i> Is that dad?</i>

264
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:15,333
Don't talk to him!

265
00:14:15,467 --> 00:14:17,367
- Jeffrey!
- Just let her!

266
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:18,500
<i> Let her!</i>

267
00:14:18,633 --> 00:14:19,867
What's wrong with you?

268
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:20,733
Give it to me!

269
00:14:20,867 --> 00:14:21,900
Give it to me!

270
00:14:22,033 --> 00:14:23,267
Dear, I'm sorry.

271
00:14:23,867 --> 00:14:25,067
So...

272
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,067
it's true?

273
00:14:27,267 --> 00:14:29,167
But why, Dad?

274
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,533
Why did you marry someone else?

275
00:14:33,433 --> 00:14:35,000
Why are you having a baby
with someone else?

276
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:37,467
It's not easy to explain, dear.

277
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:42,367
Something happened that....

278
00:14:42,933 --> 00:14:44,533
shouldn't have happened

279
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:46,300
Give it to me!

280
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:48,467
Give that to me!

281
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,367
Manuel.

282
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,433
Can you please not make it hard
for your daughter?

283
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:54,400
<i>- Let me have it, Mom.
- Please!</i>

284
00:14:54,533 --> 00:14:55,700
- Give it to me!
- Your mom is getting hurt!

285
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:57,833
Let go of it, Mom!

286
00:14:58,133 --> 00:15:00,067
Dad and I aren't done
talking yet!

287
00:15:00,367 --> 00:15:01,033
Dear.

288
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:03,033
Dear.

289
00:15:03,167 --> 00:15:04,967
Dear, listen carefully.

290
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:07,333
Remember, dear,

291
00:15:07,467 --> 00:15:10,167
that everything I do here
is for you.

292
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:12,867
For your mom, your siblings.

293
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,867
You married someone else for us?

294
00:15:16,967 --> 00:15:19,067
I don't understand.

295
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,400
<i> Andeng, Andeng, Wait.</i>

296
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:22,100
<i> Listen carefully.</i>

297
00:15:22,233 --> 00:15:25,433
Remember that no matter
what happens,

298
00:15:25,567 --> 00:15:27,633
I love you so much.

299
00:15:27,767 --> 00:15:29,767
Jeff, let go of it!

300
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:32,633
<i> Dad,</i>

301
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,400
you made a promise, didn't you?

302
00:15:36,067 --> 00:15:39,567
You promised that you'd call
and write us letters.

303
00:15:40,133 --> 00:15:42,700
You also promised
that you'd come home.

304
00:15:42,833 --> 00:15:46,100
<i>You even told me
you'd bring me to the beach.</i>

305
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:47,633
What will happen now?

306
00:15:47,767 --> 00:15:49,667
Andrea, that's not going
to happen anymore.

307
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:52,100
Dear, I'll fix this.

308
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:54,233
Jeff!

309
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:55,933
- Give it to me!
- Jeff, what are you doing?

310
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:57,100
I'll try to come home.

311
00:15:57,233 --> 00:15:59,367
- Stop making promises.
- Jeffrey!

312
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:01,900
- And stop calling
- Jeff, stop!

313
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:02,833
- from now on!
- Jeffrey?

314
00:16:02,967 --> 00:16:04,100
Jeffrey, stop it!

315
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:05,133
You don't love us anymore,
right?

316
00:16:05,267 --> 00:16:06,533
<i>- Hello, Jeffrey!
- Jeffrey!</i>

317
00:16:06,667 --> 00:16:07,800
Hello!

318
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:08,900
Hello, Jeffrey!

319
00:16:09,067 --> 00:16:10,700
Stay with your family!

320
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:12,467
Jeff!

321
00:16:14,433 --> 00:16:15,267
Son!

322
00:16:16,233 --> 00:16:16,967
Jeffrey!

323
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:17,967
Jeffrey, your mom
is getting hurt!

324
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:18,833
- Jeffrey.
- What's wrong with you?

325
00:16:18,967 --> 00:16:20,400
Jeffrey, stop!

326
00:16:54,433 --> 00:16:56,667
Why did you have to interfere,
Jeff?

327
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:59,567
You knew I was still
talking to dad!

328
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:01,067
Why do you listen to him?

329
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,467
He's a liar!

330
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,467
No!

331
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:06,167
He said he'd fix everything,

332
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:07,733
so he could come home!

333
00:17:07,867 --> 00:17:09,033
Dear, stop, that's enough.

334
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:10,400
How can he go home?

335
00:17:10,533 --> 00:17:12,333
He has another wife!

336
00:17:12,467 --> 00:17:13,933
Dad will still come home!

337
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:15,067
He will come home!

338
00:17:15,233 --> 00:17:16,267
- He won't!
- Stop!

339
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,633
Enough!

340
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:20,033
Aren't you going to stop?

341
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:24,067
Stop fighting!

342
00:17:24,767 --> 00:17:26,600
This isn't going anywhere!

343
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:29,033
Andrea, even if you
throw a fit right there,

344
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:31,500
your dad's not coming back.

345
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:34,333
We'll never be with him again.

346
00:17:36,067 --> 00:17:39,400
So just accept that he left us.

347
00:17:39,533 --> 00:17:42,500
He's gone!
He's gone!

348
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:36,733
Where did you go?

349
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,667
Did you talk to Felma again?

350
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,867
Answer me!

351
00:18:47,033 --> 00:18:48,967
If I say no,
would you believe me?

352
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,100
How dare you!

353
00:18:53,733 --> 00:18:55,700
You no longer
have respect for me.

354
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,100
My kids already know
everything, Hazel.

355
00:19:02,533 --> 00:19:03,633
Do you know how painful it is
for them?

356
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:04,467
For me?

357
00:19:05,733 --> 00:19:07,600
I heard their cry, their anger.

358
00:19:07,733 --> 00:19:09,133
But I couldn't explain to them.

359
00:19:09,267 --> 00:19:10,233
Because they're kids.

360
00:19:10,367 --> 00:19:11,800
They won't understand.

361
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:14,900
What do you want me to do?

362
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:16,233
Nothing!

363
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:18,233
You should've done nothing!

364
00:19:18,367 --> 00:19:19,700
I wish you hadn't
talked to Felma!

365
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:21,067
I wish the kids hadn't
found out!

366
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:23,200
I wish you had just let me
explain things to them,

367
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:25,467
in my own way!

368
00:19:26,733 --> 00:19:30,533
Manuel, you can go in circles
all you want,

369
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:32,333
but they'll still find out.

370
00:19:33,433 --> 00:19:35,100
You're going to hurt
your kids either way.

371
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:37,700
So if I were you,

372
00:19:38,267 --> 00:19:39,267
I'd stop sulking already.

373
00:19:40,133 --> 00:19:41,000
What's done is done.

374
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:46,700
Let them cry...

375
00:19:47,533 --> 00:19:48,533
get angry...

376
00:19:49,167 --> 00:19:50,467
squirm on the ground...

377
00:19:50,733 --> 00:19:51,733
or curse you.

378
00:19:54,967 --> 00:19:56,967
That's all they can
really do anyway.

379
00:19:58,733 --> 00:20:02,400
The truth is, they can never
take you back from me.

380
00:20:03,667 --> 00:20:04,667
So they should just accept

381
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:05,700
that you're relationship
with them is over.

382
00:20:05,833 --> 00:20:07,333
They can no longer rely on you.

383
00:20:10,833 --> 00:20:12,767
Is that really how bad you are?

384
00:20:15,267 --> 00:20:16,300
Hazel, you're going
to be a mother.

385
00:20:16,433 --> 00:20:18,633
You should be
the first one to understand.

386
00:20:19,867 --> 00:20:20,533
Okay.

387
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,267
What if I get taken away
from your child?

388
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:26,300
That's the reason
I'm doing all of this.

389
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:29,800
Because I don't want anyone
to take you away from my baby.

390
00:20:29,933 --> 00:20:32,000
But Andrea and Jeff
are not strangers.

391
00:20:32,133 --> 00:20:33,067
They are my children.

392
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,867
Illegitimate children.

393
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:37,067
Bastard children.

394
00:20:39,333 --> 00:20:40,800
Stop insulting them, Hazel.

395
00:20:40,933 --> 00:20:41,667
Why?

396
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:42,833
I'm just telling the truth.

397
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,600
And guess what, Manuel?

398
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:46,000
You did it yourself.

399
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:47,433
You made them
your illegitimate family.

400
00:20:47,567 --> 00:20:48,433
Stop!

401
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:50,733
You don't want to hear it?

402
00:20:50,867 --> 00:20:51,933
It's your fault.

403
00:20:52,433 --> 00:20:53,600
It's your fault
that they're crying

404
00:20:53,733 --> 00:20:54,667
and hurting right now.

405
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:57,067
- It's your fault!
- I said stop!

406
00:21:06,567 --> 00:21:09,000
It's your fault that they're
crying right now and hurting.

407
00:21:09,167 --> 00:21:11,200
- It's your fault!
- I said stop!

408
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:17,667
Manuel.

409
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,700
And don't you dare throw it
in my face that it's my fault.

410
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:30,500
You know the truth. I'm doing
this to save that child!

411
00:21:31,967 --> 00:21:34,800
So don't insult my children.
Do you understand?

412
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,533
And don't you dare threaten me.

413
00:21:39,467 --> 00:21:40,767
- Manuel.
- No matter what happens,

414
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:43,900
I'll find a way
to win my family back.

415
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:46,400
Manuel.

416
00:21:57,833 --> 00:21:58,733
Manuel.

417
00:21:59,833 --> 00:22:01,300
Manuel, it hurts!

418
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:08,400
Hazel!

419
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,800
Manuel, my baby!

420
00:22:14,933 --> 00:22:15,900
Manuel!

421
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,667
Manuel!

422
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,200
Here you go, Felma.

423
00:22:52,333 --> 00:22:53,633
Drink this.

424
00:22:54,667 --> 00:22:57,800
So you can let out
all your frustrations.

425
00:22:57,933 --> 00:23:00,433
I don't drink.

426
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:04,033
Believe me, Felma.

427
00:23:04,167 --> 00:23:07,867
I drink that whenever
Abel and I fight.

428
00:23:08,567 --> 00:23:11,967
It'll make you feel better.
I promise.

429
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:15,800
Manuel and I don't fight often.

430
00:23:15,933 --> 00:23:20,067
We have more beautiful
memories together.

431
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,333
Felma, cheers.

432
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,233
Come on. Just try it.

433
00:23:23,367 --> 00:23:24,467
Come on.

434
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:42,367
Doc!

435
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:44,500
- Help me!
- What happened?

436
00:23:44,633 --> 00:23:46,167
Doc, she fell on the floor.

437
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:48,500
No, no, no!

438
00:23:48,633 --> 00:23:49,833
That's not true!

439
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:51,600
He pushed me.

440
00:23:51,733 --> 00:23:52,833
No, no, no! No!

441
00:23:52,967 --> 00:23:54,700
No, I didn't mean it!

442
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:56,067
Manuel!

443
00:23:57,433 --> 00:23:59,567
Doc, help me, I think...

444
00:24:00,133 --> 00:24:02,100
I'm having contractions.

445
00:24:06,933 --> 00:24:08,133
Hazel.

446
00:24:08,267 --> 00:24:10,200
Hazel, come on.
I didn't mean it.

447
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:12,233
- Doc.
- Hazel, sorry.

448
00:24:13,067 --> 00:24:14,067
Where does it hurt?

449
00:24:14,733 --> 00:24:15,967
Here, Doc.

450
00:24:20,433 --> 00:24:24,033
How's my former love?

451
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:25,967
Are you drunk?

452
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:28,167
People change.

453
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,200
Look at you, you love
someone else now.

454
00:24:30,367 --> 00:24:31,667
I don't love Hazel.

455
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,733
You're the one I love.
You know that.

456
00:24:33,867 --> 00:24:35,067
I'm drunk.

457
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:38,500
But I'm not dumb.

458
00:24:39,033 --> 00:24:40,300
Didn't I tell you...

459
00:24:40,667 --> 00:24:42,100
to stop calling Manuel?

460
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:43,933
Our children have necessities.

461
00:24:44,067 --> 00:24:45,833
What should I call you

462
00:24:45,967 --> 00:24:47,200
if you keep forcing
yourself on him?

463
00:24:47,933 --> 00:24:49,033
Mistress?

464
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:52,933
Dad, please come home.

465
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:55,000
Who are you talking to?
Are you talking to your dad?

466
00:24:55,133 --> 00:24:56,700
I told you to stop
talking to him!

467
00:24:56,833 --> 00:24:58,000
Mom, give it to me!

468
00:24:58,133 --> 00:25:00,433
- Hello? Hello, Andeng?
<i> - I'm still talking to dad!</i>

469
00:25:00,567 --> 00:25:02,167
- Stop it!
- Andeng!

470
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:03,833
- Hello!
- We've been forbidden,

471
00:25:03,967 --> 00:25:04,867
remember?

472
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,000
Did you call Felma?

473
00:25:06,267 --> 00:25:08,200
Did you forget
what the doctor said?

474
00:25:08,833 --> 00:25:10,367
I can't get stressed out!

475
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:12,900
I'll just leave so you won't
get stressed.

476
00:25:13,033 --> 00:25:14,400
You can't leave.

477
00:25:14,633 --> 00:25:15,733
I'm alone here.

478
00:25:15,867 --> 00:25:17,433
How about me?
I'm pregnant, Manuel.

479
00:25:17,567 --> 00:25:19,367
- You can't!
- Let go of me!

480
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:20,367
Manuel!
